Iran said its forces had captured one ofIraq's strongest fortifications east of Basra on the Gulf Warsouthern front in a major battle overnight.    The Iranian National News Agency, received here, saidIranian forces smashed four Iraqi brigades, killed or wounded1,500 Iraqi soldiers and destroyed 45 enemy tanks and personnelcarriers.    IRNA said the Iranian troops seized one of the strongestIraqi fortifications and breached Iraqi defence lines southwestof Fish Lake, 10 kilometres (six miles) east of Iraq's secondlargest city of Basra. REUTER&#3;